# webi/util.kh — internal helpers shared across the webi package.
#
# str_replace(s, old, new) used to be defined here as a Khan-level
# function, since Khan's stdlib had no native string-replace builtin.
# That implementation built its result with repeated string
# concatenation (`result = result + ...`), which is O(n^2) — fine for
# short strings, but catastrophic for anything template-sized (a real
# HTML page run through render()'s {{var}} substitutions could take
# tens of seconds and peg a CPU core). str_replace is now a proper O(n)
# native in src/khan_stdlib.c instead — nothing in this file needs to
# define it anymore, and every other webi file that calls str_replace()
# (template.kh's render()/html_escape()) picks up the native
# automatically without any change on their end.
